    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the steak is done, transfer to a clean board to rest</p><p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add your <strong>beef stock</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 4-5 min or until thickened – this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> to the reserved pot with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until tender</p>",
